parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission cooler lines can cause fluid to leak out, leading to overheating of the transmission, which can result in premature wear, transmission failure, and potentially cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The transmission downshifting when the gas pedal is released can cause unexpected loss of speed, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Transmission downshifts when gas pedal is released

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the overdrive can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to loss of power, reduced fuel efficiency, and potentially cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the front differential can cause loss of traction, leading to accidents or loss of control.

The corrosion of the transmission control cable can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to loss of power, reduced fuel efficiency, and potentially cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.

Corrosion of brake lines can lead to brake fluid leaks, causing a loss of brake pressure, and potentially resulting in brake failure, which can increase the risk of accidents and put the public at risk.
symptoms: brake lines needing replacement in a short time frame.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure under prolonged use can cause a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents and putting the driver and passengers at risk.

Failure of the brake vacuum booster system can cause a loss of brake power, making it difficult to stop the vehicle, which can increase the risk of accidents and put the driver and passengers at risk.
Unusual brake noise can be a sign of a underlying brake problem, which if left unchecked, can lead to brake failure, increasing the risk of accidents and putting the driver and passengers at risk.
symptoms: Brakes make a popping sound when applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Out-of-round rear brake drums can cause uneven brake wear, leading to reduced brake performance, and potentially increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Rear brake drums need to be replaced frequently due to being out of round.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle cable can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: the vehicle stalls or loses power
the accelerator pedal feels loose or unresponsive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel gauge sending unit can cause the fuel gauge to malfunction, leading to inaccurate fuel level readings and potentially causing the driver to run out of fuel, which can lead to accidents or strand the driver.
symptoms: The fuel gauge only points to empty
the low fuel light is always lit even with a full tank of fuel

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Filter Bypass Hose Design Flaw
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the fuel filter bypass hose can cause the fuel system to receive unfiltered fuel, leading to pump failure and sudden shutdown due to lack of fuel, which can affect safety, especially in heavy traffic or critical situations.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts down due to lack of fuel
the low fuel indicator light is always on
the vehicle may stop running without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel gauge can cause the driver to be unaware of the actual fuel level, leading to unexpected fuel exhaustion and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The fuel gauge does not function properly
the low fuel indicator light is always on
the fuel level reading is inaccurate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the fuel hose/lines can allow air to enter the diesel fuel system, potentially causing engine failure or stalling, which can affect safety.
symptoms: The engine stalls or fails to start
the fuel system is contaminated with air.
